cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with spammer detection on social networks. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper discusses the use of Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA), a topic model, to extract information from text data. Additionally, it may belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper deals with natural language processing techniques. It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as spamming is a security concern on social networks. Finally, it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as social networks often involve multimedia content.
